_Huf’al_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_huf’al_ future tense]] follows these conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular*                           |\<  | *Plural*                               |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֻבְדַּל<br>_uvdal_<br>I will be separated | \< | נֻבְדַּל<br>_nuvdal_<br>We will be separated | \< |
| *Second-Person* |תֻּבְדַּל <br>_tuvdal_<br> You [male] will be separated | תֻּבְדְּלִי <br>_tuvdeli_<br> You [female] will be separated  | תֻּבְדְּלוּ <br>_tuvdelu_<br> You [males] will be separated  | תֻּבְדַּלְנָה <br>_tuvdalno_<br> You [females] will be separated  |
| *Third-Person* |יֻבְדַּל <br>_yuvdal_<br> He will be separated | תֻּבְדַּל <br>_tuvdal_<br> She will be separated  | יֻבְדְּלוּ <br>_yuvdelu_<br> [Those males] will be separated  | תֻּבְדַּלְנָה <br>_tuvdalnau_<br> [Those females] will be separated  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ב, ‎ד, and ל above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
